g.text: - Traverse the grid cell by cell
Check each cell to see it contains '1' (land) and is not visited
- Start at each unvisited land cell
When you find an unvisited '1', it represents the beginning of a new island
- Queue and enqueue the starting cell
- Dequeue a cell from the queue
- Check all four neighbors (up, down, left, right)
- If a neighbor is '1' and unvisited, mark it as visited and enqueue it
- Continue the bfs until all connected land cells are visited
